
# 🗨️ Social Media App

A **real-time chat application** for friends built with **Node.js**, **Express**, **MongoDB**, **Socket.io**, and **JWT Authentication**.  
This project provides a strong backend architecture featuring **authentication**, **middleware**, **gateway**, and **validation layers**, with **AWS S3 integration** for file storage.

---

## 🚀 Features

- 🔐 **Authentication & Authorization** using **JWT**  
- 🧩 **Modular Middleware System** for request validation and security  
- 💬 **Real-Time Communication** with **Socket.io**  
- 🧾 **Data Validation** using **Joi**  
- ☁️ **AWS S3 Integration** for storing media and assets  
- 🗄️ **MongoDB** as the primary database  
- 🧱 **Scalable Project Structure** built around controllers, services, and models  
- 🛡️ **Security Enhancements** with best practices and error handling

---

## ⚙️ Installation & Setup

Follow these steps to set up the project locally:

```bash
# 1️⃣ Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/hebaashraf55/social-media-app.git

# 2️⃣ Navigate into the project folder
cd social-media-app

# 3️⃣ Install dependencies
npm install

# 4️⃣ Create a .env file and add your environment variables
# Example:
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_aws_key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_aws_secret
AWS_BUCKET_NAME=your_bucket_name

# 5️⃣ Run the server
npm run dev


(🗂️ Folder Structure)
src/
│
├── db/                     # Database connection files
├── models/                 # Shared mongoose models
├── auth/                   # Authentication module
│   ├── controller.js
│   ├── service.js
│
├── user/                   # User-related APIs
│   ├── controller.js
│   ├── service.js
│
├── post/                   # Posts-related APIs
│   ├── controller.js
│   ├── service.js
│
├── socket/                 # Socket.io events and gateway setup
│
├── middlewares/            # Global middlewares and validation logic
│
├── utils/                  # Helper functions and constants
│
└── index.js                # App entry point

```

